# Server-1 VPN Runbook (AmneziaWG + Xray + DNS + awgctl)

Last updated: 2026-02-18

This file documents what we built on Server-1 so we can reproduce/debug and build the API next.

## Current Architecture

Client (AmneziaWG app)
-> Server-1: AmneziaWG interface `awg0` (10.66.66.1/24, UDP 51820)
-> Server-1: iptables TCP redirect (PREROUTING on `awg0`) to Xray inbound `10.66.66.1:12345`
-> Server-1: Xray outbound VLESS/REALITY to Server-2 (3X-UI)
-> Internet egress: Server-2 public IP

DNS for clients:
Client -> `dnsmasq` on Server-1 (listens on `10.66.66.1:53`) -> upstream 1.1.1.1 / 8.8.8.8

Notes:
- This setup is TCP-centric. DNS is handled. UDP apps are not guaranteed.
- AmneziaWG obfuscation parameters must match on client and server.

## Key Paths On Server-1

- AmneziaWG config: `/etc/amnezia/amneziawg/awg0.conf`
- Server public key (optional fallback file): `/etc/wireguard/awg0.pub`
- Xray config (active, symlink when failover enabled): `/usr/local/etc/xray/config.json`
- Xray primary config: `/usr/local/etc/xray/config.primary.json`
- Xray backup config: `/usr/local/etc/xray/config.backup.json`
- Xray logs: `/var/log/xray/access.log`, `/var/log/xray/error.log`
- Xray failover script: `/usr/local/sbin/xray-failover`
- Xray failover state: `/var/lib/xray-failover/state.json`
- Xray failover timer/unit: `/etc/systemd/system/xray-failover.timer`, `/etc/systemd/system/xray-failover.service`
- dnsmasq config: `/etc/dnsmasq.d/awg0.conf`
- iptables persistence: `/etc/iptables/rules.v4`
- sysctl persistence: `/etc/sysctl.d/99-forward.conf`
- awgctl binary: `/usr/local/bin/awgctl`
- vpn-agent binary (systemd ExecStart): `/usr/local/bin/vpn-agent`
- awgctl DB: `/var/lib/awgctl/db.json`
- awgctl encrypted client configs: `/var/lib/awgctl/clients/*.conf.enc`
- awgctl encryption passphrase (root-only): `/etc/awgctl/master.pass`

## Services/State Checks

### AmneziaWG (awg0)
- Show interface + peers:
  - `awg show`
- Reload interface from config (drops connections briefly):
  - `awgctl reload`

### dnsmasq
- Status:
  - `systemctl status dnsmasq --no-pager`
- Listening:
  - `ss -lunp | grep ':53'`

### Xray
- Status:
  - `systemctl status xray --no-pager`
- Listening:
  - `ss -lntp | grep ':12345'`
- Access log:
  - `tail -n 50 /var/log/xray/access.log`
- Error log:
  - `tail -n 50 /var/log/xray/error.log`
- Failover timer:
  - `systemctl status xray-failover.timer --no-pager`
- Failover logs:
  - `journalctl -u xray-failover --since "10 min ago"`
- Failover state:
  - `cat /var/lib/xray-failover/state.json`

### iptables
- PREROUTING rule exists:
  - `iptables -t nat -S PREROUTING | head`
- Counters:
  - `iptables -t nat -L PREROUTING -v -n --line-numbers`
- Anti-abuse chain:
  - `iptables -t mangle -S AWG_GUARD`
- Anti-abuse counters:
  - `iptables -t mangle -L AWG_GUARD -v -n --line-numbers`

### Anti-abuse / Anti-torrent
- Apply/re-apply guard manually:
  - `/usr/local/sbin/awg-guard-apply`
- Guard is auto-applied after `wg-quick@awg0` start via:
  - `/etc/systemd/system/wg-quick@awg0.service.d/30-awg-guard.conf`
- Current default protection:
  - block common BitTorrent/DHT ports (`6881-6999`, `6969`, `51413`, `2710`, `1337`) for TCP/UDP on `awg0`
  - limit excessive TCP connection fan-out per peer (connlimit)
  - rate-limit SYN bursts per peer (hashlimit)
  - soft shaping on `awg0` + `ifb0` using `tc cake` (fallback `fq_codel`)

